26std::string GetH264PacketizationModeOrDefault(const CodecParameterMap& params) {
27 auto it = params.find(kH264FmtpPacketizationMode);
28 if (it != params.end()) {
29 return it->second;
30 }
31 // If packetization-mode is not present, default to "0".
32 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6184#section-6.2
33 return "0";
34}
35
36bool IsSameH264PacketizationMode(const CodecParameterMap& left,
37 const CodecParameterMap& right) {
38 return GetH264PacketizationModeOrDefault(left) ==
39 GetH264PacketizationModeOrDefault(right);
40}
41
42// Some (video) codecs are actually families of codecs and rely on parameters
43// to distinguish different incompatible family members.
44bool IsSameCodecSpecific(const std::string& name1,
45 const CodecParameterMap& params1,
46 const std::string& name2,
47 const CodecParameterMap& params2) {
48 // The names might not necessarily match, so check both.
49 auto either_name_matches = [&](const std::string name) {
50 return absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, name1) ||
51 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, name2);
52 };
53 if (either_name_matches(kH264CodecName))
54 return webrtc::H264IsSameProfile(params1, params2) &&
55 IsSameH264PacketizationMode(params1, params2);
56 if (either_name_matches(kVp9CodecName))
57 return webrtc::VP9IsSameProfile(params1, params2);
58 return true;
59}

63FeedbackParams::FeedbackParams() = default;
64FeedbackParams::~FeedbackParams() = default;
65
66bool FeedbackParam::operator==(const FeedbackParam& other) const {
67 return absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(other.id(), id()) &&
68 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(other.param(), param());
69}
70
71bool FeedbackParams::operator==(const FeedbackParams& other) const {
72 return params_ == other.params_;
73}
74
75bool FeedbackParams::Has(const FeedbackParam& param) const {
76 return absl::c_linear_search(params_, param);
77}
78
79void FeedbackParams::Add(const FeedbackParam& param) {
80 if (param.id().empty()) {
81 return;
82 }
83 if (Has(param)) {
84 // Param already in |this|.
85 return;
86 }
87 params_.push_back(param);
88 RTC_CHECK(!HasDuplicateEntries());
89}
90
91void FeedbackParams::Intersect(const FeedbackParams& from) {
92 std::vector<FeedbackParam>::iterator iter_to = params_.begin();
93 while (iter_to != params_.end()) {
94 if (!from.Has(*iter_to)) {
95 iter_to = params_.erase(iter_to);
96 } else {
97 ++iter_to;
98 }
99 }
100}
101
102bool FeedbackParams::HasDuplicateEntries() const {
103 for (std::vector<FeedbackParam>::const_iterator iter = params_.begin();
104 iter != params_.end(); ++iter) {
105 for (std::vector<FeedbackParam>::const_iterator found = iter + 1;
106 found != params_.end(); ++found) {
107 if (*found == *iter) {
108 return true;
109 }
110 }
111 }
112 return false;
113}

126bool Codec::operator==(const Codec& c) const {
127 return this->id == c.id && // id is reserved in objective-c
128 name == c.name && clockrate == c.clockrate && params == c.params &&
129 feedback_params == c.feedback_params;
130}
131
132bool Codec::Matches(const Codec& codec) const {
133 // Match the codec id/name based on the typical static/dynamic name rules.
134 // Matching is case-insensitive.
135
136 // Legacy behaviour with killswitch.
137 if (webrtc::field_trial::IsDisabled(
138 "WebRTC-PayloadTypes-Lower-Dynamic-Range")) {
139 const int kMaxStaticPayloadId = 95;
140 return (id <= kMaxStaticPayloadId || codec.id <= kMaxStaticPayloadId)
141 ? (id == codec.id)
142 : (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, codec.name));
143 }
144 // We support the ranges [96, 127] and more recently [35, 65].
145 // https://www.iana.org/assignments/rtp-parameters/rtp-parameters.xhtml#rtp-parameters-1
146 // Within those ranges we match by codec name, outside by codec id.
147 const int kLowerDynamicRangeMin = 35;
148 const int kLowerDynamicRangeMax = 65;
149 const int kUpperDynamicRangeMin = 96;
150 const int kUpperDynamicRangeMax = 127;
151 const bool is_id_in_dynamic_range =
152 (id >= kLowerDynamicRangeMin && id <= kLowerDynamicRangeMax) ||
153 (id >= kUpperDynamicRangeMin && id <= kUpperDynamicRangeMax);
154 const bool is_codec_id_in_dynamic_range =
155 (codec.id >= kLowerDynamicRangeMin &&
156 codec.id <= kLowerDynamicRangeMax) ||
157 (codec.id >= kUpperDynamicRangeMin && codec.id <= kUpperDynamicRangeMax);
158 return is_id_in_dynamic_range && is_codec_id_in_dynamic_range
159 ? (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, codec.name))
160 : (id == codec.id);
161}
162
163bool Codec::MatchesCapability(
164 const webrtc::RtpCodecCapability& codec_capability) const {
165 webrtc::RtpCodecParameters codec_parameters = ToCodecParameters();
166
167 return codec_parameters.name == codec_capability.name &&
168 codec_parameters.kind == codec_capability.kind &&
169 (codec_parameters.name == cricket::kRtxCodecName ||
170 (codec_parameters.num_channels == codec_capability.num_channels &&
171 codec_parameters.clock_rate == codec_capability.clock_rate &&
172 codec_parameters.parameters == codec_capability.parameters));
173}
174
175bool Codec::GetParam(const std::string& name, std::string* out) const {
176 CodecParameterMap::const_iterator iter = params.find(name);
177 if (iter == params.end())
178 return false;
179 *out = iter->second;
180 return true;
181}
182
183bool Codec::GetParam(const std::string& name, int* out) const {
184 CodecParameterMap::const_iterator iter = params.find(name);
185 if (iter == params.end())
186 return false;
187 return rtc::FromString(iter->second, out);
188}
189
190void Codec::SetParam(const std::string& name, const std::string& value) {
191 params[name] = value;
192}
193
194void Codec::SetParam(const std::string& name, int value) {
195 params[name] = rtc::ToString(value);
196}
197
198bool Codec::RemoveParam(const std::string& name) {
199 return params.erase(name) == 1;
200}

202void Codec::AddFeedbackParam(const FeedbackParam& param) {
203 feedback_params.Add(param);
204}

206bool Codec::HasFeedbackParam(const FeedbackParam& param) const {
207 return feedback_params.Has(param);
208}
209
210void Codec::IntersectFeedbackParams(const Codec& other) {
211 feedback_params.Intersect(other.feedback_params);

214webrtc::RtpCodecParameters Codec::ToCodecParameters() const {
215 webrtc::RtpCodecParameters codec_params;
216 codec_params.payload_type = id;
217 codec_params.name = name;
218 codec_params.clock_rate = clockrate;
219 codec_params.parameters.insert(params.begin(), params.end());
220 return codec_params;
221}

223AudioCodec::AudioCodec(int id,
224 const std::string& name,
225 int clockrate,
226 int bitrate,
227 size_t channels)
228 : Codec(id, name, clockrate), bitrate(bitrate), channels(channels) {}

230AudioCodec::AudioCodec() : Codec(), bitrate(0), channels(0) {}
231
232AudioCodec::AudioCodec(const AudioCodec& c) = default;
233AudioCodec::AudioCodec(AudioCodec&& c) = default;
234AudioCodec& AudioCodec::operator=(const AudioCodec& c) = default;
235AudioCodec& AudioCodec::operator=(AudioCodec&& c) = default;
236
237bool AudioCodec::operator==(const AudioCodec& c) const {
238 return bitrate == c.bitrate && channels == c.channels && Codec::operator==(c);
239}
240
241bool AudioCodec::Matches(const AudioCodec& codec) const {
242 // If a nonzero clockrate is specified, it must match the actual clockrate.
243 // If a nonzero bitrate is specified, it must match the actual bitrate,
244 // unless the codec is VBR (0), where we just force the supplied value.
245 // The number of channels must match exactly, with the exception
246 // that channels=0 is treated synonymously as channels=1, per RFC
247 // 4566 section 6: " [The channels] parameter is OPTIONAL and may be
248 // omitted if the number of channels is one."
249 // Preference is ignored.
250 // TODO(juberti): Treat a zero clockrate as 8000Hz, the RTP default clockrate.
251 return Codec::Matches(codec) &&
252 ((codec.clockrate == 0 /*&& clockrate == 8000*/) ||
253 clockrate == codec.clockrate) &&
254 (codec.bitrate == 0 || bitrate <= 0 || bitrate == codec.bitrate) &&
255 ((codec.channels < 2 && channels < 2) || channels == codec.channels);
256}
257
258std::string AudioCodec::ToString() const {
259 char buf[256];
260 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder sb(buf);
261 sb << "AudioCodec[" << id << ":" << name << ":" << clockrate << ":" << bitrate
262 << ":" << channels << "]";
263 return sb.str();
264}
265
266webrtc::RtpCodecParameters AudioCodec::ToCodecParameters() const {
267 webrtc::RtpCodecParameters codec_params = Codec::ToCodecParameters();
268 codec_params.num_channels = static_cast<int>(channels);
269 codec_params.kind = MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO;
270 return codec_params;
271}
272
273std::string VideoCodec::ToString() const {
274 char buf[256];
275 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder sb(buf);
276 sb << "VideoCodec[" << id << ":" << name;
277 if (packetization.has_value()) {
278 sb << ":" << *packetization;
279 }
280 sb << "]";
281 return sb.str();
282}

313void VideoCodec::SetDefaultParameters() {
314 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(kH264CodecName, name)) {
315 // This default is set for all H.264 codecs created because
316 // that was the default before packetization mode support was added.
317 // TODO(hta): Move this to the places that create VideoCodecs from
318 // SDP or from knowledge of implementation capabilities.
319 SetParam(kH264FmtpPacketizationMode, "1");
320 }
321}
322
323bool VideoCodec::operator==(const VideoCodec& c) const {
324 return Codec::operator==(c) && packetization == c.packetization;
325}
326
327bool VideoCodec::Matches(const VideoCodec& other) const {
328 return Codec::Matches(other) &&
329 IsSameCodecSpecific(name, params, other.name, other.params);
330}

332absl::optional<std::string> VideoCodec::IntersectPacketization(
333 const VideoCodec& local_codec,
334 const VideoCodec& remote_codec) {
335 if (local_codec.packetization == remote_codec.packetization) {
336 return local_codec.packetization;
337 }
338 return absl::nullopt;

341VideoCodec VideoCodec::CreateRtxCodec(int rtx_payload_type,
342 int associated_payload_type) {
343 VideoCodec rtx_codec(rtx_payload_type, kRtxCodecName);
344 rtx_codec.SetParam(kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType, associated_payload_type);

347
348VideoCodec::CodecType VideoCodec::GetCodecType() const {
349 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kRedCodecName)) {
350 return CODEC_RED;
351 }
352 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kUlpfecCodecName)) {
353 return CODEC_ULPFEC;
354 }
355 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kFlexfecCodecName)) {
356 return CODEC_FLEXFEC;
357 }
358 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kRtxCodecName)) {
359 return CODEC_RTX;
360 }
361
362 return CODEC_VIDEO;
363}
364
365bool VideoCodec::ValidateCodecFormat() const {
366 if (id < 0 || id > 127) {
367 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Codec with invalid payload type: " << ToString();
368 return false;
369 }
370 if (GetCodecType() != CODEC_VIDEO) {
371 return true;
372 }
373
374 // Video validation from here on.
375 int min_bitrate = -1;
376 int max_bitrate = -1;
377 if (GetParam(kCodecParamMinBitrate, &min_bitrate) &&
378 GetParam(kCodecParamMaxBitrate, &max_bitrate)) {
379 if (max_bitrate < min_bitrate) {
380 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Codec with max < min bitrate: " << ToString();
381 return false;
382 }
383 }
384 return true;
385}

412const VideoCodec* FindMatchingCodec(
413 const std::vector<VideoCodec>& supported_codecs,
414 const VideoCodec& codec) {
415 for (const VideoCodec& supported_codec : supported_codecs) {
416 if (IsSameCodec(codec.name, codec.params, supported_codec.name,
417 supported_codec.params)) {
418 return &supported_codec;
419 }
420 }
421 return nullptr;
422}

424// TODO(crbug.com/1187565): Remove once downstream projects stopped using this
425// method in favor of SdpVideoFormat::IsSameCodec().
426bool IsSameCodec(const std::string& name1,
427 const CodecParameterMap& params1,
428 const std::string& name2,
429 const CodecParameterMap& params2) {
430 // Two codecs are considered the same if the name matches (case insensitive)
431 // and certain codec-specific parameters match.
432 return absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name1, name2) &&
433 IsSameCodecSpecific(name1, params1, name2, params2);
434}

436// If a decoder supports any H264 profile, it is implicitly assumed to also
437// support constrained base line even though it's not explicitly listed.
438void AddH264ConstrainedBaselineProfileToSupportedFormats(
439 std::vector<webrtc::SdpVideoFormat>* supported_formats) {
440 std::vector<webrtc::SdpVideoFormat> cbr_supported_formats;
441
442 // For any H264 supported profile, add the corresponding constrained baseline
443 // profile.
444 for (auto it = supported_formats->cbegin(); it != supported_formats->cend();
445 ++it) {
446 if (it->name == cricket::kH264CodecName) {
447 const absl::optional<webrtc::H264ProfileLevelId> profile_level_id =
448 webrtc::ParseSdpForH264ProfileLevelId(it->parameters);
449 if (profile_level_id &&
450 profile_level_id->profile !=
451 webrtc::H264Profile::kProfileConstrainedBaseline) {
452 webrtc::SdpVideoFormat cbp_format = *it;
453 webrtc::H264ProfileLevelId cbp_profile = *profile_level_id;
454 cbp_profile.profile = webrtc::H264Profile::kProfileConstrainedBaseline;
455 cbp_format.parameters[cricket::kH264FmtpProfileLevelId] =
456 *webrtc::H264ProfileLevelIdToString(cbp_profile);
457 cbr_supported_formats.push_back(cbp_format);
458 }
459 }
460 }
461
462 size_t original_size = supported_formats->size();
463 // ...if it's not already in the list.
464 std::copy_if(cbr_supported_formats.begin(), cbr_supported_formats.end(),
465 std::back_inserter(*supported_formats),
466 [supported_formats](const webrtc::SdpVideoFormat& format) {
467 return !format.IsCodecInList(*supported_formats);
468 });
469
470 if (supported_formats->size() > original_size) {
471 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Explicitly added H264 constrained baseline to list "
472 "of supported formats.";
473 }
474}
